comments.body:
A comment here expressing the security concerns would be nice; maybe:

// Corrections made are very conservative on purpose, to avoid
// opening up the possibility for attackers to replace valid addresses
// with look-alike addresses.

I'll add a comment. But the reason is not that it allows attackers anything. The corrections were already very conservative and limited to what base58 considers equivalent, so there was already no risk of look-alike addresses.

More like:

  // Corrections made are very conservative on purpose, to avoid
  // users unexpectedly getting away with typos that would normally
  // be detected, and thus sending to the wrong address.
